summary: I think the thing I like about the Detective Pikachu movie is that it seems like a lot of the unnecessary exposition is going to...
body: I think the thing I like about the Detective Pikachu movie is that it seems like a lot of the unnecessary exposition is going to be left out. It assumes you know Pokemon. The world-building is visual, stuff in the background that is intuitive. You see those Golurk in the background and you automatically know they’re standing guard. That’s going let the story focus on the characters and plot rather then going out of its way to explain what’s going on in that world.

title: Pokemon is Legal Dog Fighting!
body:
For all of y’all out there thinking that the new Pokemon Live Action looks awful, well it is so there you go!

Pokemon:

-You go out into the woods and throw rocks or a plastic ball at a pokemon that is just minding its own business.

-Once captured, that pokemon must now obey your commands

-You take your pokemon to fights and tournaments and show it off

-You pit your pokemon against others for badges, money, supplies etc

-Once your pokemon is beaten within an inch of its life, you return it to sit inside of a ball where you take it, throw it on a tray and give it to Nurse Joy.

-She restores the pokemon to full health and then you start the entire process over again.

-You leave your pokemon with random strangers to “look after” and can sometimes leave your pokemon with these people for months at a time. Meanwhile, if they aren’t in someone’s care, they’re just stuck inside of a pokeball with no way to escape and the pokemon have no free will of their own

-so bascially:

#MEW-TWO WAS RIGHT!!!!
